<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Serena Williams survived a first set scare before hitting top form and progressing into the last-16 of the US Open.</p>

<p>Williams was outplayed by American compatriot Sloane Stephens in the first set but eventually powered through at the Arthur Ashe Stadium to win 2-6 6-2 6-2.</p>

<p>The six-time winner will now take on Maria Sakkari in the fourth round hoping to book a spot in the quarter-finals.</p>

<p>The Greek 15th seed had already progressed earlier on following a 6-3 6-1 victory over American Amanda Anisimova.</p>

<p>More to follow... </p>

